    "slug": "future-council-comments-on-mogadishu-negotiations",
    "summary": "The Future Council issued a statement on talks between the Federal Government and regional states. The group called for a return to dialogue and broader representation.",
    "content": "The Future Council (Golaha Mustaqbalka), a coalition of Somali civil society and political figures, released a statement commenting on the recent negotiations between the Federal Government of Somalia and regional state leaders in Mogadishu. The talks, held earlier this month, aimed to resolve ongoing political disputes over electoral reforms and power-sharing arrangements.\n\nIn its statement, the Future Council acknowledged the importance of the discussions but expressed concern over their inclusivity. The group urged all parties to expand the dialogue to include opposition groups, traditional elders, and women's organizations to ensure a more representative outcome. It also emphasized the need for transparency and adherence to the agreed-upon timelines for elections.\n\nThe negotiations come amid heightened political tensions in Somalia, with disagreements over the implementation of the 2018 electoral model and the extension of presidential terms. The Federal Government has defended the talks as a step toward stability, while some regional administrations have criticized the pace of reform.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, these developments are closely watched as they affect stability and governance in the homeland. Many diaspora members invest in Somalia and advocate for inclusive political processes. The Future Council's call for broader participation resonates with those seeking durable peace and democratic progress.\n\nThe group concluded its statement by reaffirming its commitment to mediating further discussions and supporting any agreement that leads to a stable, representative government.\n\nRead the original report from Horseed Media here: https://horseedmedia.net/golaha-mustaqbalka-oo-ka-hadlay-wadahadallada-muqdisho/423543/",
